k is a small sample of the talks that Ajahn Sumedho offered during the winter retreat of 2001. The aim of the editors in compiling this book has been explicitly to maintain the style and spirit of the spoken word. As Ajahn Sumedho himself commented, "The 
book is meant to be suggestions of ways to investigate conscious experience. It's not meant to be a didactic treatise on Pali Buddhism." 
\par }{\f1\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid6644223 \line }{\f1\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid6644223\charrsid6644223 (1,188 KB) The Noble Eightfold Path - The Way to the End of Suffering \emdash  Bhikkhu Bodhi. 
