\par These are insightful teachings by a Lay Thai women teacher, Kee Nanayon (1901-1978); who
 established a Dhamma centre, Khao-Suan-Luang in 1945. Upasika Kee attracted Dhamma students, and residents came to include both female lay devotees and white-robed nuns. These Dhamma talks were mainly given to the women who stayed at her centre to practi
ce meditation. After listening with calm and centred mind, they would all sit in meditation together. 
